(1549, 101, 5, 'Please introduce yourself in English (about 100 words).', NULL, 'My name is XXX,and I am a student at XX University,majoring in Computer Science. I was born in XXX City. I love programming,reading and playing basketball. In my spare time,I enjoy learning new things,especially in the field of AI. My goal is to become a good software engineer who can contribute to society. I work hard and never give up. I am also a friendly and outgoing person who likes making friends. Thank you for listening.', '自我介绍模板', 5.00, 1, 104),
(1550, 101, 5, 'Please write a short essay on ''The Importance of Learning English''.', NULL, 'English is one of the most important languages in the world. First,it is widely used in business and academic communication. Almost all international conferences and journals use English. Second,learning English helps us access global information and culture. Most websites,books,and movies are in English. Third,English skills are crucial for our career. Many companies require English proficiency. In conclusion,learning English broadens our horizons and creates more opportunities. We should keep working on it.', '学英语重要性', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1551, 101, 5, 'Please describe your favorite hobby in English.', NULL, 'My favorite hobby is reading. I started reading at the age of 6 when my parents gave me a children''s storybook. Now I read various books,including novels,history,and technology. Reading helps me relax after a busy day and broadens my knowledge. I particularly enjoy reading at night before bed. My favorite book is ''The Three-Body Problem''. Through reading,I have learned about different cultures and ways of thinking. I plan to read at least 30 books this year.', '爱好描述', 5.00, 1, 104),
(1552, 101, 5, 'Please write an email to your friend, inviting him to your birthday party.', NULL, 'Dear John,I hope this email finds you well. I am writing to invite you to my birthday party next Saturday at 6 p.m. The party will be held at my home. We will have dinner,play games,and watch a movie together. Many of our old friends will be there too. It would be wonderful if you could join us. Please let me know if you can come. Looking forward to seeing you. Best regards,Tom', '邀请信', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1553, 101, 5, 'Please briefly describe a memorable trip you have had.', NULL, 'Last summer,I went to Beijing with my family. It was my first time visiting the capital. We visited the Great Wall,the Forbidden City,and Tiananmen Square. The Great Wall impressed me the most because of its magnificent view and rich history. We also tried Peking Duck,which was delicious. The trip lasted five days,during which we took many photos and made wonderful memories. I learned a lot about Chinese history and culture. I would love to visit Beijing again in the future.', '旅行描述', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1554, 101, 5, 'What are the basic English tenses? Briefly explain.', NULL, 'English has 16 tenses,formed by combining 4 time references (present,past,future,past future) with 4 aspects (simple,continuous,perfect,perfect continuous). The most common ones include: 1) Simple present (I work); 2) Simple past (I worked); 3) Simple future (I will work); 4) Present continuous (I am working); 5) Past continuous (I was working); 6) Present perfect (I have worked); 7) Past perfect (I had worked). Each tense expresses a specific time and aspect of action.', '英语时态', 5.00, 3, 104),
(1555, 101, 5, 'Please explain the structure of an English sentence.', NULL, 'An English sentence usually has 5 basic structures: 1) S+V (Subject + Verb): He runs. 2) S+V+O (Subject + Verb + Object): I love English. 3) S+V+P (Subject + Linking Verb + Predicative): She is happy. 4) S+V+IO+DO (Subject + Verb + Indirect Object + Direct Object): He gave me a book. 5) S+V+O+OC (Subject + Verb + Object + Object Complement): They made him happy. Sentences can be combined into compound or complex sentences using conjunctions or relative pronouns.', '英语句子结构', 5.00, 3, 104),
(1556, 101, 5, 'Please explain the difference between active voice and passive voice.', NULL, '1) Active voice: The subject performs the action. Structure: S + V + O. Example: ''Tom wrote the letter.'' Used to emphasize the doer. 2) Passive voice: The subject receives the action. Structure: S + be + V-ed (+ by + agent). Example: ''The letter was written by Tom.'' Used when: a) the doer is unknown or unimportant; b) we want to emphasize the receiver; c) in scientific or formal writing. Conversion: Active object becomes passive subject,verb changes to ''be + past participle''.', '主动被动', 5.00, 3, 104),
(1557, 101, 5, 'Please explain when to use the present perfect tense.', NULL, 'Present perfect (have/has + V-ed) is used when: 1) An action started in the past and continues to now: ''I have lived here for 10 years.'' 2) An action just completed with present relevance: ''I have finished my homework.'' 3) Past experience without specific time: ''I have been to Paris.'' 4) With time markers: already,yet,ever,never,just,recently,since,for. Compared to simple past: simple past emphasizes ''when''; present perfect emphasizes ''now''.', '现在完成时', 5.00, 3, 104),
(1558, 101, 5, 'Please describe a useful English study method.', NULL, 'Effective English study methods include: 1) Vocabulary: Learn 20 new words daily and review systematically using apps like Anki; 2) Listening: Watch English movies/TV shows with subtitles,then without. Listen to podcasts (TED,BBC); 3) Speaking: Find a language partner,use shadowing technique. Don''t fear mistakes; 4) Reading: Start with simple novels,gradually increase difficulty. Read newspapers (China Daily); 5) Writing: Keep a daily diary in English,write essays on topics; 6) Grammar: Don''t memorize rules - use it. Combine input (listen/read) and output (speak/write).', '学习方法', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1559, 101, 5, 'Please briefly compare British English and American English.', NULL, 'Differences between British (BrE) and American English (AmE): 1) Spelling: colour/color,centre/center,theatre/theater,organise/organize. 2) Vocabulary: lift/elevator,lorry/truck,biscuit/cookie,flat/apartment,holiday/vacation. 3) Pronunciation: BrE ''r'' is silent at end of words; AmE pronounces ''r''. 4) Grammar: BrE uses present perfect more often; AmE uses simple past more. 5) Date format: BrE day/month/year; AmE month/day/year. Both are mutually intelligible. Choose one and stick to it for consistency.', '英美英语', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1560, 101, 5, 'What is your dream job and why?', NULL, 'My dream job is to be a software engineer specializing in artificial intelligence. There are several reasons. First,I love coding and have been programming since high school. The feeling of bringing ideas to life through code is amazing. Second,AI is transforming the world. From self-driving cars to ChatGPT,AI applications are everywhere,and I want to be part of this revolution. Third,this career offers good salary and growth opportunities. To achieve this dream,I am studying computer science,learning machine learning,and doing internships at tech companies.', '梦想工作', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1561, 101, 5, 'Please describe your hometown.', NULL, 'My hometown is XX,a beautiful city in eastern China. It has a population of about 10 million. The city has a long history of over 2000 years and many historical sites. The climate is mild,with four distinct seasons. Spring is full of flowers,summer is hot,autumn is cool with golden leaves,and winter is sometimes snowy. The local cuisine is famous,especially XX dishes. People are friendly and hardworking. In recent years,the city has developed rapidly with modern buildings and convenient transportation. I love my hometown and miss it very much.', '家乡描述', 5.00, 1, 104),
(1562, 101, 5, 'Please briefly explain what ''Internet'' is.', NULL, 'The Internet is a global network connecting millions of computers worldwide. It allows people to communicate,share information,and access services online. Key features: 1) Global connectivity through TCP/IP protocols; 2) Offers various services: email,web browsing,social media,video streaming,online shopping; 3) Decentralized architecture - no single point of control; 4) Built on the World Wide Web (WWW),which uses HTTP/HTTPS. Major impacts include transforming education (online learning),business (e-commerce),and society (social media). The Internet has become an essential part of modern life.', '互联网', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1563, 101, 5, 'Please write a short complaint letter about a defective product.', NULL, 'Dear Sir/Madam,I am writing to complain about a smartphone I purchased from your online store on March 15. The phone arrived with a cracked screen and a malfunctioning camera. Despite following the user manual,the phone shuts down randomly. The order number is XYZ-12345. I would like to request a full refund or replacement of the defective product. I have attached photos as evidence. I expect your prompt response within 7 days. Looking forward to your reply. Sincerely,John Smith', '投诉信', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1564, 101, 5, 'What advice would you give to a junior student about university life?', NULL, 'My advice to a junior student: 1) Time management: balance studies and social life. Use a planner and prioritize tasks; 2) Active learning: don''t just attend classes - participate,ask questions,study with peers; 3) Build relationships: make friends and connect with professors. Networks help you grow; 4) Try new things: join clubs,attend events,explore hobbies. University is for self-discovery; 5) Take care of health: exercise,eat well,sleep enough. Mental health matters; 6) Plan ahead: think about your career goals early; 7) Don''t fear failure - it''s part of learning. Good luck!', '建议信', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1565, 101, 5, 'Please explain the importance of teamwork.', NULL, 'Teamwork is essential in modern society. First,it brings together diverse skills and perspectives. Different team members contribute their strengths,leading to better solutions than individuals alone. Second,teamwork increases productivity. Tasks divided among team members can be completed faster. Third,it fosters communication and interpersonal skills,which are crucial in workplace. Fourth,teamwork creates a sense of belonging and motivation. Members support each other through challenges. However,effective teamwork requires good leadership,clear roles,and mutual respect. In conclusion,mastering teamwork is a key skill for success in any career.', '团队合作', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1566, 101, 5, 'Please describe a person who has influenced you the most.', NULL, 'The person who has influenced me the most is my father. He is a teacher who has been working in education for over 30 years. He has taught me three important things: First,the value of hard work. He always tells me ''No pain,no gain''. Second,the importance of integrity. He insists on doing the right thing even when no one is watching. Third,the love of learning. He still reads books every day at the age of 60. Whenever I face difficulties,I think of him and find strength. I am deeply grateful for his guidance and love.', '重要的人', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1567, 101, 5, 'Please write about your view on online learning.', NULL, 'Online learning has become widespread,especially after COVID-19. It has both advantages and disadvantages. Advantages: 1) Flexibility: learn anytime,anywhere; 2) Variety: access to global courses (Coursera,edX); 3) Cost-effective: cheaper than traditional courses; 4) Self-paced: students can learn at their own speed. Disadvantages: 1) Lack of face-to-face interaction; 2) Requires self-discipline; 3) Technology issues; 4) Difficulty in staying focused. In my opinion,online learning is a valuable supplement to traditional education. The best approach is to combine both online and offline methods.', '在线学习', 5.00, 2, 104),
(1568, 101, 5, 'Please describe your future plans.', NULL, 'In the next 5 years,I plan to: First,complete my undergraduate studies with excellent grades and pass CET-6. Second,do internships at top tech companies during summer vacations to gain practical experience. Third,prepare for graduate school,focusing on AI or software engineering. After graduation,I plan to work for 2-3 years in industry to apply what I learned. In the long term,I want to start my own tech company that solves real social problems. To achieve these goals,I will keep learning,building skills,and networking with talented people. Hard work and persistence are key.', '未来计划', 5.00, 2, 104),
